# Code quality, formatting and conventions

- Run `make verify` to verify formatting and vet checks pass before committing
- Run `make test` to ensure tests pass before committing
- Run `make codegen` after modifying API types to regenerate clients, listers, informers, and deepcopy
- Run `make vendor` after changing dependencies to update the vendor directory
- Always use "When ... it should ..." format for describing test cases when creating unit tests
- Always include unit tests when creating new functions or modifying existing ones
